 relatively easy on the scale of epic difficulty.<br><br>2)If Solomen dropped all three staves, every wizard in Norrath would have their epic.<br> <p><center><img src=http://members.fortunecity.com/jwolf47//sitebuildercontent/sitebuilderpictures/zam.jpg></center><center>"Above all Shadows, rides the Sun"</center><center><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=273965>[My Stuff]</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/utheperfectflaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ThePerfectFlaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Druidhugger</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/1/02 8:48:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2957.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizard Epic Question...</span><hr size=1> You mean every wizard doesn't already have it?   I thought it was issued to you soon as you dinged 51, kinda like the monk and cleric epics.  8(<br><br><br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Edit: sig deleted - too big. Rules are: 150 high, 450 wide, no greater than 50kb.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ualbarath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Albarath</A> at: 8/1/02 11:38:14 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/utheperfectflaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ThePerfectFlaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Druidhugger</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/1/02 8:50:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2957.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizard Epic Question...</span><hr size=1> But as far as MQ'ing it goes, I'd -highly- suggest against it.  For alot of people it's worked, and for an equal number of people it hasn't.<br><br>And I believe now that handing stuff in while invis no longer works?  If so, you'd have to find people to MQ with who haven't gotten their epics.  Once you do your own epic, your truespirit faction = in the tubes.<br><br><br><br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Edit: sig deleted - too big. Rules are: 150 high, 450 wide, no greater than 50kb.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ualbarath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Albarath</A> at: 8/1/02 11:39:37 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/usnowfootcoldtoes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>snowfoot coldtoes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/1/02 2:21:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2957.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizard Epic Question...</span><hr size=1> MQing not an issue as long as the person doing it has good faction.<br><br>What I stress and I really really really stress is pay attention to the MQ!!!   Make sure the person who is MQing a staff or 2 with you has said &quot;okay I have handed in my staff(ves), now you hand in your staff(ves).&quot;<br><br>This happened to a wizard I was MQing with last week.  he jumped the gun and handed in his staves before I handed in the phiny staff.  When I handed in the phiny staff....bam...I get the final hand in bag for wizard epic.  /sigh   Now I have this bag in inventory hoping against the odds the wizard can possibly get help from CS on this.  Right...dinks they are never help on MQing stuff but one can hope.<br><br>Remember:  MQ at your own risk and PAY ATTENTION TO THE PERSON MQING IT WITH YOU!!!<br><br> <p>______________________Snowfoot Coldtoes60 Orac